.TH "yama_ptracer_add" 9 "yama_ptracer_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
yama_ptracer_add \- add/replace an exception for this tracer/tracee pair
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" yama_ptracer_add
.BI "(struct task_struct *tracer "  ","
.BI "struct task_struct *tracee "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tracer" 12
the task_struct of the process doing the ptrace
.IP "tracee" 12
the task_struct of the process to be ptraced
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Each tracee can have, at most, one tracer registered. Each time this
is called, the prior registered tracer will be replaced for the tracee.

Returns 0 if relationship was added, -ve on error.
